The paper deals with secure network coding, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves communication networks, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses graph theory to represent the network, which is a topic covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
